column70: COMPETITIVE GRANTS: PROMOTING K-12 STUDENT ACHIEVEMENT AT MILITARY-CONNECTED SCHOOLS
column73: THIS PROPOSAL SEEKS TO ADDRESS AN UPWARD TREND LINE OF SCHOOL-TIME DISCIPLINE INCIDENTS AMONG MILITARY-CONNECTED STUDENTS. TO ADDRESS THIS COMMUNITY-WIDE CONCERN, WHEATLAND SCHOOL DISTRICT IS OFFERING A NEW SERVICE, CALLED PALS (PLAY AND LEARN SQUAD), TO OUR K-8TH GRADE STUDENTS ATTENDING BEAR RIVER SCHOOL, LONE TREE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL, AND WHEATLAND CHARTER ACADEMY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA. PALS WILL FILL A GAP IN OUR CURRENT MULTI-TIERED SYSTEM OF SUPPORT BY PROVIDING STUDENTS WITH REGULARLY SCHEDULED AND INTENTIONAL STRATEGIES THAT PREPARE THEM FOR WORK LIFE BALANCE THROUGH THE APPLICATION OF HEALTHY PHYSICAL AND MINDFUL WELLNESS ACTIVITIES AND PRACTICES IN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL. IT IS DESIGNED TO SUPPORT STUDENTS VIA INCREASING EDUCATIONAL CONTINUITY, BUILDING LIFE-LONG SOCIAL-EMOTIONAL SKILL SETS AND DEVELOPING HEALTHY PHYSICAL ACTIVITY HABITS. USING BEST PRACTICES LEARNED FROM THE BRAIN SCIENCES, RESEARCH-BASED CURRICULUM AND OUR EXPERIENCES WORKING WITH MILITARY-CONNECTED STUDENTS, PALS AIMS TO: (1) INCREASE PHYSICAL ACTIVITY IN A STUDENT-CENTERED MANNER THROUGH DIRECT INSTRUCTION USING A COOPERATIVE COMMUNITY/PLAY MODEL (2) EMPOWER STUDENTS WITH SOCIAL-EMOTIONAL SKILL SET PRACTICE THAT DEVELOP THEIR INTERPERSONAL CAPACITY, FOSTER A GROWTH MINDSET, AND ENHANCE VIEWPOINT REFLECTIONS THROUGH INTEGRATED LESSONS ACROSS THE CAMPUS YIELDING A SCHOOL COMMUNITY COMMON LANGUAGE/CULTURE, (3) MOTIVE STUDENTS TO CONDUCT THEMSELVES AND MAKE CHOICES THAT GUIDE THEM TOWARD POSITIVE PHYSICAL AND MENTAL HEALTH, AND (4) GROW STUDENT SELF-REGULATION SKILLS THAT TIE BACK TO PERSONAL HEALTH, WORKFORCE CAPACITY, COOPERATIVE COMMUNITY AND INTERPERSONAL CAPACITY FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF SELF-ASSURED INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE POSITIVE CONTRIBUTORS TO THEIR COMMUNITY'S SYNERGY.

column70: COMPETITIVE GRANTS: PROMOTING K-12 STUDENT ACHIEVEMENT AT MILITARY-CONNECTED SCHOOLS
column73: STEAMING INTO HEALTH SCIENCES WILL BE IMPLEMENTED AT 5 SCHOOLS WITHIN THE CHULA VISTA ELEMENTARY SCHOOL DISTRICT IN SAN DIEGO COUNTY. PROJECT GOALS ARE TO 1 INCREASE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL STUDENTS EXPOSURE TO CAREERS IN THE HEALTH SCIENCES, 2 IMPROVE 4TH GRADE STUDENTS AWARENESS AND KNOWLEDGE OF HEALTH SCIENCE CAREERS AND HOW THESE CAREERS ALIGN WITH THEIR STRENGTHS AND INTERESTS, AND 3 IMPROVE CAASPP CAST PERFORMANCE OF 5TH GRADE STUDENTS WHO EXPERIENCED THE HEALTH STATION, AFTER-SCHOOL STEM SESSIONS AND STEM SUMMER CAMP. STRATEGIES THAT WILL BE DELIVERED TO STUDENTS AND SUPPORTED BY TEACHER PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT ARE PROJECT-BASED AND WORK-BASED LEARNING ACTIVITIES THROUGH A HEALTH STATION EXPERIENCE IN CLASS TECHNOLOGY SUPPORT THROUGH A PERSONALIZED LEARNING PLATFORM TO HELP KIDS IDENTIFY STRENGTHS, INTERESTS, AND CAREER ASPIRATIONS AND EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES THROUGH AFTER SCHOOL STEM CLUBS AND STEM SUMMER CAMP.
column77: INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT

column70: COMPETITIVE GRANTS: PROMOTING K-12 STUDENT ACHIEVEMENT AT MILITARY-CONNECTED SCHOOLS
column73: SILVER VALLEY UNIFIED SCHOOL DISTRICT PROPOSES A FIVE-YEAR, 1.5 MILLION GRANT ENTITLED S.H.A.P.E LEARNING: STRENGTHENING HEALTH ACADEMICS PHYSICAL EMOTIONAL LEARNING. THIS PROJECT WILL FOSTER MILITARY-CONNECTED STUDENTS' HEALTH SCIENCES FOUNDATIONAL SKILLS THROUGH BUILDING SOCIAL EMOTIONAL LEARNING, ACADEMIC COMPETENCIES IN MATH, AND OVERALL WELLNESS. LOCATED IN A REMOTE AREA IN CALIFORNIA'S MOJAVE DESERT, SVUSD SERVES 75.5% MILITARY-CONNECTED STUDENTS FROM FORT IRWIN NATIONAL TRAINING CENTER AND THE MARINE CORPS LOGISTICS BASE BARSTOW. THROUGH THIS PROJECT, SVUSD WILL ADDRESS IDENTIFIED MILITARY-CONNECTED STUDENT NEEDS AND BARRIERS TO THEIR ACADEMIC SUCCESS. THE PROJECT GOALS ARE: 1. INCREASE THE PERCENTAGE OF MILITARY CONNECTED 3RD - 5TH GRADERS WHO MEET OR EXCEED STANDARDS ON THE STATE MATH ASSESSMENT AND 2. DECREASE THE PERCENTAGE OF MILITARY-CONNECTED 8TH GRADERS WHO ARE SUSPENDED. SVUSD MILITARY-CONNECTED STUDENTS HAVE GAPS IN BOTH THESE AREAS COMPARED TO PEERS ACROSS THE STATE. TO ACCOMPLISH THIS, SVUSD WILL IMPLEMENT THREE STRATEGIES: 1. IN-CLASS CURRICULUM AND INSTRUCTION SUPPORT: ROBUST TEACHER PROFESSIONAL LEARNING AND COACHING IN MATH AND SOCIAL EMOTIONAL LEARNING (SEL) ENHANCE TOOLS FOR P.E. INCLUDING YOGA CURRICULUM AND AN HOLISTIC WELLNESS FOCUS WELLNESS SPACES FOR USE BY CLASSES AND SMALL GROUPS WHO NEED TARGET SUPPORT. 2. IN-CLASS TECHNOLOGY SUPPORTS: STUDENTS' MATH SKILL WILL DEVELOP WITH INDIVIDUALIZED EXACT PATH SUPPORT TECHNOLOGY TOOLS ENHANCE WELLNESS CURRICULUM LAPTOPS FOR MIDDLE SCHOOL STUDENTS ALLOW ACCESS EXACT PATH AND SEL CURRICULUM. 3. EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES: AFTERSCHOOL WELLNESS ACTIVITIES INCLUDE SEL TOPICS, YOGA, AND SPORTS GROUPS FAMILY WELLNESS NIGHT AT FORT IRWIN, STEAM FILED TRIPS FOR 4TH GRADERS.
